type":"text","text":"Today we are going to talk about the Mind Builder and see how Little Nita makes plans as we revisit the book "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Little Nita’s Big Idea, "}]},{"type":"text","text":"written by Anna W. Bardaus and illustrated by Carolina Farias."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the Clifford Puppet."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Clifford knows that making plans helps us reach a goal. He likes to read narratives about plans and reaching goals."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Close-Read: Connect to the Mind Builder"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s reread and talk about how Nita makes a plan to reach her goal—to make the biggest fruit salad in the world!"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Equity Sticks during reading to choose children to respond."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 2–3"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why do you think making the world’s biggest fruit salad sounds like lots of fun? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 6–7"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Nita plans to have her neighbors help her, but they cannot. Show me with your face how you think she feels when no one can help her. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold"